'
LLaMA (Large Language Model Meta AI) is a state-of-the-art foundational large language model designed to help researchers advance their work in natural language processing (NLP). It is designed to be smaller and more performant than other large language models, making it easier to retrain and fine-tune for specific potential product use cases. LLaMA works by taking a sequence of words as an input and predicting a next word to recursively generate text. It is trained on a large set of unlabeled data, which makes it ideal for fine-tuning for a variety of tasks. LLaMA is available in several sizes (7B, 13B, 33B, and 65B parameters) and a model card is available that details how it was built.

'
The machine learning algorithm used to train LLaMA is a natural language processing (NLP) system. This type of algorithm is used to process and analyze large amounts of text data in order to generate meaningful insights. It is also used to create predictive models that can be used to make decisions or predictions about future events.
